==English==

===Etymology===
From the French Imperial forename ''[[Napoleon]]'', usually with reference to [[w:Napoleon Bonaparte|Napoleon Bonaparte]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/nə'pəʊlɪən/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#  a gold [[coin]] worth twenty [[franc]]s issued by Napoleon I; a twenty-franc coin
#:*'''1891''': We had occasion some months ago to strengthen our resources, and borrowed, for that purpose, thirty thousand '''napoleons''' from the Bank of France. — Arthur Conan Doyle, ‘The Red-Headed League’ (Norton 2005 p.67)